<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLATFORM; ARM THE RAFT PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KARNA SMALL BODMAN was senior director of the National Security Council in 
the Reagan White House. She told The Times: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In Cuba, as in Haiti, the real answer to these tragedies lies with the people 
themselves, not in some notion of U.S. troops acting either as a landing force 
or welfare support group. Guantanamo Bay is actually a training base, or at 
least it was.So let's get it back on line; let's make an announcement to all 
those strong, dedicated Cubans who braved sharks and 10-foot waves that they 
can volunteer to be trained at Guantanamo to form a force that one day will 
free their people from Fidel Castro's grip. 
</P>
<P>
 In spite of almost universal disdain, Castro has been able to remain in power 
because he is protected by personal security troops, numbering 10,000 by some 
estimates. Remember, there are more than 20,000 Cubans at Guantanamo already, 
plus another million or so living in Florida who just might welcome a chance to 
participate in bringing down Castro. 
</P>
<P>
 As the training began to turn out an elite fighting corps, word could be 
beamed to the people of Cuba that help is finally on the way, help from their 
own husbands and sons -- who better to liberate their country? 
</P>
</TEXT>
