<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOXING; GRIFFIN REMAINS UNBEATEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montell Griffin of Chicago outpointed Ray Lathon of St. Louis in a 12-round 
unanimous decision Monday night in a bout matching undefeated light 
heavyweights at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Montell Griffin of Chicago outpointed Ray Lathon of St. Louis in a 12-round 
unanimous decision Monday night in a bout matching undefeated light 
heavyweights at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Griffin (14-0), a 1992 Olympian, had a 115-111 margin on all three judges' 
cards. Lathon is 14-1. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Former world champions Michael Nunn and Simon Brown won their first fights 
since being dethroned this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Nunn (43-2, 28 KOs), who lost his WBA super middleweight title in February, 
knocked out Mexico's Salvador Maciel (19-6) with a left uppercut to the eye 54 
seconds into the first round of their scheduled 10-round bout at the Silver 
Nugget Casino in North Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown (42-3) had a tougher time with Maciel's brother, Nestor (24-6), rallying 
in the final three rounds to take a close but unanimous 10-round decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
