<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANUCKS GIVE KING ROOKIE COLD GREETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rookie centers Mike Peca and Rick Girard had goals and Pavel Bure had three 
assists in the Vancouver Canucks' 5-1 exhibition victory over the Kings on 
Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Adams, Jose Charbonneau and Brian Glynn also scored for the Canucks.Ken 
Hodge scored for the Kings. 
</P>
<P>
 King rookie goalie Jamie Storr, selected seventh overall in the 1994 draft, 
gave up all five goals after replacing rookie starter Pauli Jaks midway through 
the second period. 
</P>
<P>
 Adams opened the scoring late in the second period, beating Storr with a high 
backhand off a rebound on a two-man advantage. Girard, Charbonneau and Peca 
gave Vancouver a 4-0 lead before Hodge scored at 14:43 of the third. 
</P>
<P>
 Glynn completed the scoring on the power play with 2:17 left. 
</P>
