 Cincinnati Red outfielder Deion Sanders surrendered to city police on new 
charges related to his scuffle with a police officer Aug. 8 at Riverfront 
Stadium. Sanders' lawyer said he will plead innocent. . . . Marc Kroon struck 
out 13 to lead Rancho Cucamonga to a 3-1 victory over Modesto in the California 
League championship series opener. . . . Bill Pulsipher threw the first 
no-hitter in an Eastern League playoff game in 57 years in Binghamton's 2-0 
victory over Harrisburg. . . . Matt Alcone of Laguna Beach and Jerry Gilbreath 
won the Superboat Racing Championship on Sunday in Miami Beach, Fla., in a 
record of 113.5 m.p.h. . . . Shefonda Colbert, a starter for the Cal State 
Fullerton women's basketball team, has been academically disqualified. 
