<TEXT>
<P>
 After a dull offensive effort that both quarterback Wayne Cook and Coach Terry 
Donahue said could have been brightened by the presence of wide receiver J.J. 
Stokes, Donahue said Monday that he expected to have Stokes back for Saturday's 
game at Nebraska. 
</P>
