<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; LONEKER WILL GO ON INJURED RESERVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Starting left guard Keith Loneker is expected to go on the injured-reserve 
list and undergo surgery for a fallen left arch, Coach Chuck Knox said. 
</P>
<P>
 Loneker, a second-year player, injured his arch in the Rams' 31-13 loss at 
Atlanta on Sunday.Tom Newberry, the starting left guard last season and the 
backup center to Bern Brostek this year, is expected to replace Loneker. 
</P>
<P>
 Loneker's injury also will mean more playing time for Chuck Belin. The Rams 
projected big things from Belin during the exhibition season but he has been 
inactive for the first two regular-season games. 
</P>
<P>
 Knox also said the team might explore signing a free agent offensive lineman 
to add depth. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ram quarterback Chris Miller, asked if he would have wanted to stay in Atlanta 
rather than sign with the Rams in the off-season: "I would have liked to play 
for (Atlanta Coach) June Jones. I like the city here. . . . but things change 
-- I'm out West for at least a year, until we get shipped out somewhere else." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tank Younger, Tex Schramm, Tom Fears and Elroy Hirsch are among 14 former Ram 
players who will serve as honorary captains at the coin toss of Sunday's game 
against San Francisco at Anaheim Stadium. The Rams will wear replica uniforms 
from their 1951 NFL championship season in Sunday's "throwback game" to honor 
the 75th anniversary of the NFL. 
</P>
<P>
 The former Ram players also will be honored in a halftime ceremony. MIKE 
REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
