1994 PREP PREVIEW: GIRLS' TENNIS; SIX TEAMS TO WATCH; EL MODENA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Jim Schultz (first year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: 16-2, 9-1; lost to Laguna Beach in the Southern Section Division II 
quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Brandi Freudenberg, Sr., advanced to section singles semifinals 
last year, will play No. 1 singles; Holli Freudenberg, So., will play No. 2 or 
No. 3 singles; Talline Kojian, So., will play doubles; Amy Medlin, Jr., will 
play No. 2 or No. 3 singles; Julie Yoshikawa, Sr., will play doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Yu Chang, Jr., will play doubles; Susanne Cowan, So., will play 
doubles; Kellie Medigovich, So., will play doubles with junior Anjula Narang; 
Mary Rasch, Sr., will play doubles; Joanna Zafra, Jr., will play doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Usually when coaches retire, they leave the cupboard bare for the new 
coach. Not in this case. Art Green left Schultz, his assistant of three years, 
perhaps the most talented team in the county. Schultz says the Freudenberg 
sisters and Medlin are playing the best tennis of their lives. If the young 
doubles teams come together, El Modena will challenge for the Division II 
title. 
