<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Bob Walton (ninth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: 22-3, 10-0 in Pacific Coast League; Division II champion for the second 
consecutive year, beating Edison, 11-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Michelle Bray, Jr.; ranked 18th in Southern California girls' 
16 division, will play No. 1 singles; Amanda Hastings-Phillips, Jr., will play 
No. 2 singles and maybe some doubles; Lindsay Weiss, Jr., will play No. 2 or 
No. 3 singles; Sarah Cohen, Jr.; will play No. 1 doubles; Vanessa Zajfen, So.; 
will probably play No. 2 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Stacey Kirner (), Sr., returns after missing last year; Kim 
Woodhouse, Fr., will play doubles; Summer Terry, Fr., will play doubles; Trini 
Jessoe, Fr. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Walton petitioned to move his two-time Southern Section Division II 
champions to Division I so they could battle Palos Verdes Peninsula. But when 
the Southern Section ruled that the entire Pacific Coast League would have to 
move up, Laguna Beach and the PCL decided to stay put. Too bad for Division II 
because the Artists are loaded again. "Now that we're still in Division II, the 
girls see the opportunity is there and the goal is there to win a third title," 
he said. 
</P>
