<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; WOMAN ROBBED IN MALL PARKING LOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Thousand Oaks woman was robbed of her wedding ring and other jewelry Monday 
afternoon in The Oaks mall parking lot by a man who threatened her with a metal 
object against her neck. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Ann Wells, 31, ran to the Bullocks department store after the assailant 
took her wedding ring, watch and diamond bracelet at about 12:45 p.m. at 222 W. 
Hillcrest Drive, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Ron Tusi said the suspect, believed to be in his 20s, approached Wells 
from behind while she was standing at the open driver-side door of her car. The 
man put a metal object against the back of her neck, Tusi said, while telling 
her to hand over her jewelry. 
</P>
<P>
 She did and he fled north on foot through the parking lot, toward Hillcrest 
Drive, Tusi said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, who eluded authorities despite an extensive search, was described as 
having blond hair and wearing a green flannel shirt, with a tattoo of barbed 
wire on his right wrist, Tusi said. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
