<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; ADULT SCHOOL SEEKS LITERACY 
VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley Adult School Literacy Program is seeking volunteers to tutor 
adults in basic literacy skills. 
</P>
<P>
 Tutors -- who do not need a background in teaching -- will be expected to work 
with adult students for a minimum of two hours a week, during weekdays or 
evenings, at the adult school's literacy center. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have a program well-established that has up to 90 tutors during the school 
year," said Literacy Coordinator Marge Ceran. "(But) during the fall classes we 
try to get about 25 new tutors." 
</P>
<P>
 Tutors work one-on-one with students, teaching reading, writing, spelling and 
speaking skills, Ceran said. During the past two years, the literacy program 
has served about 105 students annually.  
</P>
<P>
 A free workshop for interested volunteers will be held from 8:30 a.m. to 3:30 
p.m. Saturday, Oct. 1, at the adult school's learning center, 1025 Old Farm 
Road in Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call 374-1161. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
