<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: DEMOCRATS TO OPEN CAMPAIGN OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNETH R. WEISS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A united group of local Democrats on Thursday will open a Democratic 
headquarters in Ventura for the fall election campaigns of various state 
legislative and congressional candidates. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County headquarters, located at the Old Sawyer College building at 
470 Thompson Blvd. in Ventura, will be shared by campaigns of gubernatorial 
candidate Kathleen Brown, congressional candidate Kevin Ready, state Senate 
candidate Jack O'Connell and Assembly candidate Mindy Lorenz. 
</P>
<P>
 Democrats United, a fund-raising organization, is helping finance the county 
headquarters and will have staff there to help coordinate precinct canvassing 
and efforts to get Democrats to the polls on election day. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are expecting a hundred to 200 people Thursday evening," said Ron 
Pembleton, a Lorenz campaign aide. Lorenz, O'Connell and Ready are scheduled to 
attend the grand opening from 5 to 7 p.m., he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited, but organizers request a $5 donation. For more 
information, call 643-9906. KENNETH R. WEISS 
</P>
</TEXT>
