<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; WOMAN KILLED IN CRASH IS IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An elderly Ventura woman who was killed in a traffic accident near Mugu Rock 
while being shuttled home from an Alaskan cruise has been identified as 
Virginia Lorraine Danford. 
</P>
<P>
 Danford, 75, was killed in a multi-car accident Saturday night that stopped 
traffic on Pacific Coast Highway for about two hours. 
</P>
<P>
 She and her friend, 75-year-old Grace Toy of Ventura, were passengers in a car 
operated by a local shuttle service that had picked them up at Los Angeles 
International Airport, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Coroner Craig Stevens said the two had taken a flight from Vancouver, 
British Columbia, after a 10-day Alaskan cruise. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred when a van traveling south on Pacific Coast Highway spun 
out of control and careened into their northbound car, which in turn was struck 
by another northbound vehicle, Officer Brian DeMattia of the California Highway 
Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Toy, who was taken to St. John's Pleasant Valley Hospital in Camarillo, was 
reported in fair condition Monday night. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
