<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; 2 MEN IN DRUG BUST TO BE ARRAIGNED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Anaheim men who were arrested in Ventura during a joint undercover 
operation that snared about $60,000 worth of cocaine and heroin are to be 
arraigned today in Ventura County Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 Alejandro M. Hernandez, 23, and Jerardo M. Contreras, 20, were being held 
Monday in Ventura County Jail in lieu of $100,000 bail, sheriff's Sgt. Fred 
Bustillo said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two were arrested Friday in the Toys-R-Us parking lot at Johnson Drive and 
Ventura Road, where authorities also seized a kilogram of cocaine and an ounce 
of tar heroine from the front seat of their pickup truck, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the drugs they confiscated, authorities raided a house in 
Orange County and seized more than $25,000 in cash, all of it in small 
denominations, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is more for street users," Lt. Pat Miller of the Ventura Police 
Department said of the seized drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 He added that the suspects were believed to be couriers for an organized group 
in Anaheim that has been selling to Ventura County drug users "for some time." 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects, who had arranged to sell the drugs to an undercover officer at 
the parking lot, were targets of the newly formed Ventura-Oxnard Narcotic 
Enforcement Team. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller said the team includes officials from the Ventura and Oxnard police 
departments, the Ventura County Sheriff's Department, the FBI and the federal 
Drug Enforcement Administration. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
