but his move to running back is proving to be a productive switch. McGraw 
carried the ball 27 times for 277 yards and six touchdowns, tying the Orange 
County single-game record for rushing touchdowns in a 48-26 victory over 
Sonora.He scored on runs of 22, 51, 61, 27, one and four yards. Laguna Hills 
Coach Steve Bresnahan said McGraw benefits from a strong offensive line. "I'm 
not going to say every time he carries the ball we block really good," 
