<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Heather Garritson 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park, Freshman 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 Garritson quickly lived up to the family name. In her first high school 
competition, she broke the freshman record at the Laguna Hills Invitational by 
37 seconds, winning the three-mile race in 17:41.Sister Carrie, now at Alabama, 
set the sophomore record of 16:53 in 1991. Heather Garritson said she started 
training harder late this summer. "We just dropped my sister off at Alabama a 
couple weeks ago, and after that I started trying to keep up with my brother 
(Garrett, a Buena Park junior) in workouts," she said. Now the rest of Orange 
County high school runners will have to try to keep up with her. 
</P>
