<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; D.A. SETS 
UP SPECIAL UNIT TARGETING REAL ESTATE FRAUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dist. Atty. Gil Garcetti on Monday announced creation of a special unit that 
will prosecute real estate fraud, vowing to put behind bars scam artists who 
rob a vulnerable segment of society."Real estate fraud preys on the elderly. It 
preys on low-income families," Garcetti said. 
</P>
<P>
 The unit, made up of three deputy district attorneys and three investigators, 
is funded for its first year with $500,000 from the Federal Home Loan Mortgage 
Corp. and the Mortgage Insurance Companies of America. 
</P>
<P>
 The unit is one of two funded from outside the district attorney's office 
after a standoff with the County Board of Supervisors was resolved in April, 
freeing up funds. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Don Tamura, the head of the new unit, said it already is 
tackling 14 cases, including one in which a man with multiple sclerosis was 
kicked out of his home under false pretenses and is now living in his car. 
</P>
