<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; INQUIRY INTO FATAL CRASH CONTINUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies were continuing their investigation Monday into a 
two-vehicle weekend accident that killed a 20-year-old Littlerock man and 
seriously injured a 17-year-old Palmdale youth. 
</P>
<P>
 The 17-year-old lost control of his van Sunday afternoon while heading north 
on 47th Street East in Palmdale, deputies said.The van slid across the road 
near the intersection of Avenue S and hit a pickup truck driven by Leslie 
Chenard, 34, of Hesperia, according to authorities. Chenard was unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
 Upon impact, both the driver of the van and his passenger, Pablo Beltran, 20, 
of Littlerock, were thrown from the vehicle. Neither was wearing a seat belt, 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Beltran was pronounced dead at Palmdale Hospital Medical Center. The 
17-year-old was being treated at the hospital for hip and facial injuries, a 
nursing supervisor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
