<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents will have an opportunity to question City Council candidates during 
a forum at City Hall tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 School board and water district candidates will also introduce themselves at 
the forum, which starts at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by Village Laguna, one of the city's oldest political action 
committees, the forum will be televised at a later date. 
</P>
<P>
 Village Laguna President Gary Jenkins said 10 candidates were invited to 
attend, regardless of whether they are seeking the group's endorsement. About 
half of them had confirmed as of Monday, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum will be televised later on Dimension Cable, Channel 31. However, 
Jenkins said the exact date has not been set. 
</P>
<P>
 Three council terms will expire this year. Mayor Ann Christoph is the only 
incumbent seeking reelection. 
</P>
<P>
 Village Laguna was formed in 1971 to preserve the city's village atmosphere 
and fight development of high-rise buildings along the city's coast. 
</P>
