<TEXT>
<P>
 Russia to Upgrade Antiquated Phone System: The first phase of the $40-billion 
project will be launched in early 1995.Three Western partners -- US West of 
Englewood, Colo., Germany's Deutsche Telekom and France Telecom -- are expected 
to sign a memorandum of intent on Oct. 10 in Moscow. The three agreed to invest 
$600 million in the first phase of the project. It will connect 50 Russian 
cities with 30,000 miles of fiber-optic cable to create a modern 
telecommunications network and allow the installation of 20 million new 
telephones within 10 years. 
