delays by the EPA already threaten current EPA-sponsored meetings with the auto 
makers, environmental groups and the states that are intended to avoid lawsuits 
and other slowdowns to cutting air pollution. Though it had been expected to 
act, the EPA did not give notice on the proposal last Friday or Monday. 
