<P>
 Lucky Employees Continue Working: About 1,700 warehouse employees and drivers 
for Lucky Stores reported for work Monday without a contract after all-night 
negotiations averted a strike at the supermarket chain's 235 Southern 
California stores but failed to produce an agreement.Letting a 12:01 a.m. 
strike deadline pass, negotiators for the Teamsters and Lucky talked through 
the night and returned to the bargaining table later in the day to meet with a 
federal mediator over issues of job security, work preservation and flexible 
workweeks. "There's no extension of the contract. We're just going day-to-day," 
said Ed Mireles, head of Teamsters Local 952 in Orange, shortly before heading 
into a 5 p.m. session. 
