ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Where does the money go? 
</P>
<P>
 Some may question how finances can be considered "tight" in a school district 
spending nearly $100 million this school year. 
</P>
<P>
 In the 21,500-student Irvine Unified School District, most of the 
$98.7-million budget is spent on employee salaries and benefits, similar to 
public school districts throughout the state. 
</P>
<P>
 In Irvine, 80% of the budget, or $79 million, will go to district teachers and 
classified employees. About $2.9 million -- or 3% of the budget -- will be 
spent on supplies for the district's 31 schools. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Today is the last time the Fullerton Downtown Planning Committee will meet to 
review design guidelines for the city's downtown. The nine-member group was 
created by the City Council to study designs for businesses and come up with 
recommendations to improve the downtown economic environment, city officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Some of the guidelines committee members will discuss at today's meeting 
include signs, architecture, landscaping and trees. The public is encouraged to 
attend the meeting, which will be at Rutabegorz Restaurant, 211 Pomona Ave., at 
7 p.m. 
</P>
