<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYPRESS MOURNS RESIDENT KILLED IN USAIR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David D. Garber, a city resident who was killed in the crash of a USAir jet 
near Pittsburgh, Pa., on Sept. 6, was remembered during a brief ceremony that 
opened Monday's City Council meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 In a solemn opening to the meeting, Mayor Richard Partin praised Garber, a 
two-term member of the city Traffic Commission, for his service to the city, 
and said residents mourned his loss. 
</P>
<P>
 Garber was one of 132 people who perished when the aircraft suddenly plummeted 
to earth a few miles from the airport. 
</P>
<P>
 Garber, who was first appointed to the commission in 1987, showed a special 
interest in creating and maintaining city bicycle trails, Partin said. 
</P>
<P>
 "God bless you, David," Partin said. "We're going to miss you." 
</P>
