<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUARTERLY EARNINGS DROP AT DICK CLARK PRODUCTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dick Clark Productions Inc., a Burbank television production company, said its 
earnings in its fourth fiscal quarter that ended June 30 were $502,000, down 
44% from $900,000 in the fiscal fourth quarter of 1993. Revenues for the 
quarter were $12.4 million, down 19% from $15.4 million the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the year, earnings were $5.1 million, up 59% from $3.2 million in 1993. 
Revenues were $58.3 million, up 34% from $43.4 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the lower fourth-quarter results to a decline in its 
television and corporate production business. Th dip was partly offset by gains 
in its restaurant sales stemming from the opening of two new American Bandstand 
Grill restaurants in the Midwest during the fourth quarter. 
</P>
