<P>
CALIFORNIA AMPLIFIER'S PROFIT CLIMBS SLIGHTLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California Amplifier, the Camarillo-based maker of equipment for beaming 
television signals, said its profit for the second quarter that ended Aug. 27 
was $550,000, up slightly from $544,000 for the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenues for the quarter were $11.32 million, up 11% from $10.18 million last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, California Amplifier's profit fell 12% to $956,000 from 
$1.08 million for the first six months a year prior. The slip was on a 20% gain 
in revenue to $22.51 million from $18.76 million last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed these results to a $611,000 increase in research and 
development spending over the six months aimed at broadening its product line 
in wireless cable technology. 
</P>
