REGIONAL ROUNDUP: NEXTEL OFFERS TO BUY AMERICAN MOBILE SHARES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 American Mobile Systems Inc. in Woodland Hills said Nextel Communications 
Inc., a wireless communications company, has offered to purchase all the 
American Mobile shares it doesn't already own for about $73 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Nextel earlier agreed to acquire up to 65% of American Mobile equity for a 
combination of cash and properties in Florida.It currently owns about 9% of 
American Mobile's shares. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the new proposal, Rutherford, N.J.-based Nextel would issue 3 million of 
its common shares, currently valued at more than $24 a share, in exchange for 
all of American Mobile's outstanding shares. 
</P>
<P>
 The acquisition of American Mobile is part of Nextel's plan to build a 
nationwide wireless communications system. Its plans were dealt a setback last 
month when MCI Communications Corp. canceled a $1.3-billion marketing deal that 
would have linked its long-distance service with Nextel. 
</P>
