<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW / JACK SEARLES: FIRM HAS A HIT TRACKING CALLS TO PUBLIC 
UTILITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oasis Technology Inc., a Camarillo software firm, has carved out a niche 
producing systems that track and analyze customers' calls to public utilities. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, Oasis began helping Southern California Gas Co. computerize 
information about such calls. 
</P>
<P>
 That project is continuing, reports Oasis President George Baldonado, and 
additional contracts have recently been received from the state's two local 
telephone companies, Pacific Bell and GTE California. 
</P>
<P>
 "We expect most of the calls to be complaints about billing or service," 
Baldonado said. "We'll create a system that will track customers' previous 
problems and how they were resolved. We'll also help analyze trends, showing 
regions or types of service where problems tend to arise." 
</P>
<P>
 Oasis, which expects sales of about $5 million this year, has been ranked by 
Hispanic Business magazine as one of the nation's leading Latino-owned 
companies. 
</P>
